Operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, Enugu Command have arrested nine suspected internet fraudsters at the Premier Layout, Ogui Nike axis of Enugu State. A statement issued by EFCC’s spokesman, Wilson Uwujaren on Friday named the suspects’ Napoleon Providence, Udenta Arinze, Chidiebere Jonas, Ezeh Obinna, Imonikphawae Lucky, Arinze Ugochukwu, Anieze Sylvester, Okonkwo Ifeanyi Evans, and Ogugua Sopuruchukwu. He said the suspects were all arrested based on verified intelligence which linked them with fraudulent impersonation and other forms of cybercrimes targeting unsuspecting foreign nationals. Ex-Zambian President, Banda Dies Of Cancer At 85 Gowon Flags Off Construction Of British-American Junction… “Items recovered from the suspects include several phones, 5 laptops, a Mercedes Benz car, Lexus RX330 and a Toyota Camry 2009. “The suspects will be charged to court as soon as investigations are concluded,” he said.